Head 0.5–0.6 × as long as wide, covered with dense punctures and dark brown setae. Clypeus 0.5 × as long as wide, slightly convex in lateral view. Face 0.5 × as long as wide, convex medially (
Fig. 15
). Length of malar space 0.5–0.6 × as long as basal mandibular width. Mandible not strongly twisted. OOL 0.7–0.9 × as long as POL. Antenna with 74–79 flagellomeres. FL1 2.0–2.2 × as long as FL2. Apical flagellomeres not widened, length more than width (or same).

Metasoma weakly polished, more or less shagreened, covered with fine and sparse punctures, dull surface (
Fig. 16
). T1 2.4–2.6 × as long as maximum width, covered with minute and transverse striae basally. T2 1.0–1.1 × as long as maximum width. T4-T7 weakly compressed. Ovipositor sheath 0.3 × as long as hind tibia, weakly widened apically, covered with brown setae.

Colouration (
Figs 14–16
). Body (excluding wings and legs) black, except for: clypeus sometimes tinged with whitish-brown ventrally; mandible with whitish-yellow spot dorsomedially; mandibular teeth tinged with reddishbrown; antenna with a median white band; medial part of collar sometimes tinged with whitish-yellow; subalar prominence sometimes tinged with reddish-brown; scutellum with a yellow spot; ovipositor reddish-brown. Wings hyaline. Veins and pterostigma blackish-brown except for yellowish-brown wing base. Legs black to blackishbrown except for: fore and mid femora, tibia and tarsus partly tinged with brown to yellowish-brown; apical part of second tarsomere, third and fourth tarsomeres whitish-yellow to white. Sometimes apical part of hind first tarsomere also whitish-yellow to white.

Male (n=112). Similar to female. Face 0.5–0.6 × as long as wide. OOL 0.9–1.0 × as long as POL. Length of malar space 0.5–0.7 × as long as basal mandibular width. Antenna with 65–71 flagellomeres. FL1 1.7–1.8 × as long as FL2. Hind femur 7.0–7.3 × as long as maximum depth in lateral view. Hind first tarsomere 2.2–2.4 × as long as second tarsomere. T1 2.4–2.7 × as long as maximum width. Punctures on metasomal tergites denser than female. Clypeus yellow to whitish-yellow dorsally (
Fig. 18
). Face with a pair of yellow to whitish-yellow stripes along inner margin (
Fig. 18
). Mandible with a large whitish-yellow area basally (
Fig. 18
). Ventral surface of scape sometimes yellow to whitish-yellow. Yellow area on collar larger than female but not as enlarged as in 

E. compressus


sp. nov.

Posterodorsal corner of pronotum, subalar prominence and tegula whitish-yellow (
Fig. 17
). Fore and mid coxae and trochanters with a conspicuous whitish-yellow marking. Hind fifth tarsomere yellow to whitish-yellow (
Fig. 17
). Posterior margin of metasomal tergites sometimes tinged with reddish-brown. Fore and mid legs paler than female (
Fig. 17
).
